{
  "texts": [
    "IntroductionSince the advent of artificial intelligence (AI) research, some researchers have expressed concern that AI systems might become more intelligent than humans, with eventually fatal outcomes for humanity [1,2].",
    "In recent years, these worries have intensified [3,4].",
    "Perhaps the strongest piece of evidence of the growing concern is a statement released by the Center for AI Safety earlier this year.",
    "The statement consisted only in one sentence: \"Mitigating the risk of extinction from AI should be a global priority alongside other societal-scale risks such as pandemics and nuclear war\" [5].",
    "While many other researchers disagreed publicly, the statement was signed by a long list of researchers in AI and related fields, including the deep learning luminaries Geoffrey Hinton and Joshua Bengio.In this paper, I will evaluate approaches for dealing with catastrophic risks from AI."
  ]
}